    "summary": "As organisation development consultant I help leadership of mission driven entreprises with often multi-complex development questions. \nI facilitate and design strategic change processes, retreats and learning journeys for mission driven leaders and organizations. \nMy recent years at Triodos Bank and FMO have left me with a warm heart for values based financial institutions. Working with entrepreneurs and leaders of organizations energizes me. Contributing to meaningful transformation makes me smile.\n\nCurrently, I advices leadership of mission driven enterprises on growth issues, strategy, and the impulse of their organisation. As part of the leadership of the Institute for Social Banking I help to develop the training offer of this network organisation of European mission driven banks.\n\nRecent experiences include FMO, the Dutch development bank, where I worked together with the Director Strategy. My responsabilities included the learning and development strategy 2020 - 2025, leadership development for the top 75 of the bank and the development of learning offers for clients and stakeholders as part of the COVID-19 response package, together with the Capacity Development department.\n\nFrom 2015 till mid 2019 I worked as Group Manager Learning and Development of Triodos Bank, the world\u2019s leading sustainable financial institution. In this role I was responsible for the group-wide learning activities of the 1400+ co-workers. I built up the Triodos Academy and created initiatives that foster a lean, living, learning organizational culture, with a well-embedded mission throughout all layers of the organization. \n\nBuilding on a ten year carreer in documentary film making and cultural entrepeneurship (2000 \u2013 2010) I started working as organization advisor at IMO \u2013 Instituut voor Mens en Organisatie-ontwikkeling. I worked in fields varying from health care and financials, to media production companies and social enterprises. As core group member I contributed to IMO\u2019s Methodology of the Evidential, and the Horizontal Leadership concepts (2010-2015). \n\nAs project leader of the Green Film Making Project I worked on bringing a sustainable innovation approach to the Dutch film sector (2011-2014). \n\nI am fascinated by the complexity of human individuals working together to bring their ideals to life.\nWith a constant attention for processes, dialogue and the biography of the individual and of the organisation I support, I aim to contribute to  the development of strategic visions, and help to create the right initiatives to make vision reality. \n\n",
